data.chText: （对新观点、建议等）愿意倾听的，乐于接受的
data.enText: willing to listen to or to accept new ideas or suggestions

data.chText: 她总是愿意接受新观点。
data.enText: She was always receptive to new ideas.

data.chText: 他做了一次感人的讲演，听众深受感动。
data.enText: He gave an impressive speech to a receptive audience.

simple_means.memory_skill: re 一再 + cept 拿 + ive 有…性质的 → 一拿再拿 → 善于接受的

means: (对新观点、建议等)愿意倾听的

tr: of a nerve fiber or impulse originating outside and passing toward the central nervous system
open to arguments, ideas, or change
example: receptive to reason and the logic of facts

tr: ready or willing to receive favorably

value.def: Someone who is receptive to new ideas or suggestions is prepared to consider them or accept them.

example.ex: The voters had seemed receptive to his ideas...
example.tran: 选民看上去很愿意接受他的想法。

example.ex: Do you think that there is any receptive audience for his remarks.
example.tran: 你觉得有人愿意接受他的言论吗？

value.tran: （对新思想或建议）乐于接受的，能接纳的，善于听取的

example.ex: There was less receptiveness to liberalism in some areas.
example.tran: 在一些地区自由主义并不怎么受欢迎。

example.ex: There was a lack of receptivity to the advances in science.
example.tran: 对于科学的进步还缺少接纳能力。

value.def: If someone who is ill is receptive to treatment, they start to get better when they are given treatment.

example.ex: ...those patients who are not receptive to treatment.
example.tran: 治疗未见效果的那些病人

value.tran: （对治疗）反应良好的，能接纳的
